text:
<!channel> - Awhile back, <@U026NB2U2>, <@U02HCCTFL> and I were invited to the planning portion of a "Build-a-thon" put on by the University of Oregon's Agora Journalism Center here in Portland. <@U02618EV1> took part in the actual building portion, which has been captured in an article and video with a quick shot of Gaston building. 

Fantastic not only to see it here, but to be part of this sort of thing from the get go. Thanks <@U02618EV1> for representing us, as always. 

<http://www.pbs.org/mediashift/2015/05/turning-data-into-civic-tools-journalists-coders-students-collaborate-in-portland/>

attachments.text: The University of Oregon School of Journalism and Communication’s Agora Journalism Center hosted “Storytelling with Data Build-a-thon,” a three-day event bringing journalists, coders, designers and students to collaborate on data-driven tools and stories.Addressed were five civic topics: housing, education, earthquake preparedness, campaign finance and economic innovation.
